Oh please.

157
00:07:03,506 --> 00:07:04,507
[laughs]

158
00:07:04,590 --> 00:07:07,009
‎这身肉给了你都不知道从哪下手
You wouldn't know what to do with this.

159
00:07:08,386 --> 00:07:12,849
‎雷德在楼上放了一个巨大的木雕驼鹿
No. Red has a giant wooden moose
in the upstairs closet.

160
00:07:12,932 --> 00:07:15,101
‎多年来 我一直想把它扔了
And I've been trying
to get rid of it for years,

161
00:07:15,184 --> 00:07:17,145
‎但太沉了 我搬不动
but it's too heavy for me to lift.

162
00:07:17,228 --> 00:07:19,730
‎没问题 有男人帮忙 就不用问我了
Oh sure. Don't ask me
because you need a man to help.

163
00:07:19,814 --> 00:07:21,649
‎冷静 埃莉诺罗斯福
Oh, calm down, Eleanor Roosevelt.

164
00:07:21,732 --> 00:07:24,735
‎我只想把那个蠢东西弄走
I just want the stupid thing
out of the house.

165
00:07:24,819 --> 00:07:25,820
‎好吧
Okay.

166
00:07:25,903 --> 00:07:28,698
‎你去搬驼鹿 我继续在这里帮忙
Go get the moose,
and I'll keep helping down here.

167
00:07:28,781 --> 00:07:29,782
‎交给我
On it.

168
00:07:30,533 --> 00:07:33,661
‎你能描述一下这只木头驼鹿吗？
Can you describe this wooden moose to me?

169
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:35,538
‎就是只驼鹿
It's a moose.

170
00:07:39,041 --> 00:07:40,585
‎不过是木头做的
But made of wood.

171
00:07:42,253 --> 00:07:43,296
‎我会尽力的
I'll do my best.

172
00:07:46,883 --> 00:07:48,426
‎太糟糕了
This sucks.

173
00:07:48,509 --> 00:07:51,137
‎昨天我吻杰伊的时候还很自在
Yesterday I was totally comfortable
kissing Jay.

174
00:07:51,220 --> 00:07:54,557
‎你现在就像一个不想被人抱的娃娃
[chuckles] Now you look like a baby
that doesn't want to get picked up.

175
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:55,600
‎我知道我干了啥！
I know what I did!

176
00:07:57,268 --> 00:07:59,645
‎对不起 我有点过意不去
Oh, I'm sorry. I feel bad.

177
00:08:00,563 --> 00:08:03,774
‎我只是想给你建议 不是让你伤脑筋
I was trying to give you advice,
not break your brain.

178
00:08:04,692 --> 00:08:05,860
‎我需要建议
I need advice.

179
00:08:05,943 --> 00:08:08,446
‎杰伊有很多经验
Jay has a lot of experience.

180
00:08:08,529 --> 00:08:10,156
‎我最接近嘿咻的一次
The closest I've come to having sex

181
00:08:10,239 --> 00:08:12,533
‎是在划水槽上 裤头卡了屁股
is when I got a front wedgie
on a Slip 'N Slide.

182
00:08:13,242 --> 00:08:14,744
‎嗯 头得先进去
Yeah. You gotta go headfirst.

183
00:08:14,827 --> 00:08:15,828
‎我就是那样做的
I did.

184
00:08:16,454 --> 00:08:18,456
‎我朋友的妈妈是机械工程师
My friend's mom is a mechanical engineer.

185
00:08:18,539 --> 00:08:19,999
‎她都懵了
She was baffled.

186
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:22,043
‎听着 别想太多
Look, don't overthink it.

187
00:08:22,126 --> 00:08:25,004
‎顺其自然吧 只是别碰他的头发
Just do what comes naturally.
Except don't touch his hair.

188
00:08:25,087 --> 00:08:27,673
‎我一碰内特的头发
‎就触发了裤头里的开关
If I go near Nate's hair,
it flips a switch in his pants.

189
00:08:28,341 --> 00:08:29,425
‎还有开关？
There's a switch?

190
00:08:29,926 --> 00:08:31,802
‎男孩子真是太复杂了
These boys are so complicated!

191
00:08:31,886 --> 00:08:33,221
‎才没有呢
They're really not.

192
00:08:33,930 --> 00:08:36,265
‎把手放在他屁股上
Just put your hands on his hips.

193
00:08:36,349 --> 00:08:39,185
‎距离够近 他知道你感兴趣
It's close enough to the good stuff
so he knows that you're interested,

194
00:08:39,268 --> 00:08:41,854
‎但又保持距离 让他明白你没有出手
but far enough away
so he knows you're not making a move.

195
00:08:42,605 --> 00:08:43,648
‎明白了
Got it.

196
00:08:43,731 --> 00:08:46,234
‎亲亲往后摸 拉链管拉锁
Lips are for hips
like zippers are for zips.

197
00:08:47,735 --> 00:08:49,278
‎我是这么记州府的
It's how I learned my state capitals.

198
00:08:49,987 --> 00:08:51,447
‎别再这样了
Never do that again.

199
00:08:53,407 --> 00:08:54,825
‎-中大奖了
‎-你找到了？
-Jackpot.
-You found it?

200
00:08:55,618 --> 00:08:58,538
‎没有 我找到了一整箱万圣节旧服装
No, I found a whole box
of old Halloween costumes.

201
00:08:59,372 --> 00:09:01,207
‎应该是只蜜蜂
I think this is supposed to be a bee.

202
00:09:01,832 --> 00:09:04,460
‎可怜的福尔曼太太 你尽力了
Oh, Mrs. Forman, bless your heart.
You tried.

203
00:09:04,961 --> 00:09:07,755
‎奥兹 别闹了 我们不是在扮家家
Ozzie, stop messing around.
We're not playing dress-up.

204
00:09:07,838 --> 00:09:09,966
‎那就把你找到那件旧外套脱了
Then take off that old jacket you found.

205
00:09:10,049 --> 00:09:12,468
‎拜托 我穿着超像克里斯蒂安史莱特
Come on. Makes me look
like Christian Slater.

206
00:09:13,261 --> 00:09:15,429
‎咱俩想的肯定
‎不是同一个克里斯蒂安史莱特
We must be thinking of
different Christian Slaters.

207
00:09:17,682 --> 00:09:18,766
‎快看！
[Ozzie] Oh look!

208
00:09:19,559 --> 00:09:21,727
‎好得很 找到了
Oh! Sweet. You found it.

209
00:09:24,188 --> 00:09:28,484
‎你今天经历了精彩冒险呢
‎小包包 我们回家吧
You have had quite the adventure today,
little baggie. Let's get you home.

210
00:09:30,278 --> 00:09:32,905
‎你们在我家车库做什么？
-What are you doing in my garage?
-Uh…

211
00:09:32,989 --> 00:09:34,574
‎我们在等你
We were… waiting for you.

212
00:09:34,657 --> 00:09:35,741
‎你迟到了
You're late.

213
00:09:36,617 --> 00:09:38,494
‎福尔曼先生 说说你今天过得怎么样
Tell us about your day, Mr. Forman.

214
00:09:40,204 --> 00:09:42,832
‎好了 现在你们该走了
All right, this is when you leave.

215
00:09:44,458 --> 00:09:46,085
‎把外套还我
And give me that jacket.

216
00:09:46,168 --> 00:09:51,299
‎这可是我1964年
‎在西尔斯百货花全价买的
I paid full price for that thing
at Sears in 1964.

217
00:09:57,471 --> 00:09:58,973
‎滚出我的车库
Get out of my garage.

218
00:09:59,056 --> 00:10:00,600
‎你们属于地下室！
You're basement people!

219
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:04,020
[rock music playing]

220
00:10:05,479 --> 00:10:06,397
[Nate strains]

221
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:09,483
‎-是这个吗？
‎-不 是另一个
-Is this it?
-No, it's the other one.

222
00:10:09,567 --> 00:10:10,943
‎我搞错了
Oh, my bad.

223
00:10:11,027 --> 00:10:12,486
‎没有 我开玩笑的
No, I'm kidding, I'm kidding.

224
00:10:12,570 --> 00:10:13,779
[laughs]

225
00:10:13,863 --> 00:10:15,531
‎他开玩笑没用的
You can't do that with him.

226
00:10:16,115 --> 00:10:18,075
‎-好大
‎-好重
-That is big.
-And heavy.

227
00:10:18,159 --> 00:10:19,410
‎还蠢到家
And stupid.

228
00:10:22,622 --> 00:10:23,831
‎（阪神虎）

229
00:10:23,914 --> 00:10:26,250
‎等等…那是我爸爸寄给我的衬衫
Wait… That's the shirt my dad sent me.

230
00:10:26,334 --> 00:10:28,461
‎你把它弄得脏兮兮 还给剪了
You got stuff all over it and cut it up.

231
00:10:28,544 --> 00:10:30,713
‎反正对你来说也太小了
‎就像咱家的淋浴一样
It's too small for you, anyway.
Just like our shower.

232
00:10:30,796 --> 00:10:33,507
‎我听见你在浴室里叮铃咣啷
‎就像只掉进垃圾箱的狗熊
I hear you banging around in there
like a bear that fell in a dumpster.

233
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:36,260
‎我那叫动感淋浴
I take an athletic shower.

234
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:39,680
‎别试图转换话题
‎你不能随便碰我的东西
And don't try to change the subject.
You can't just touch my stuff.

235
00:10:39,764 --> 00:10:41,807
‎你是说像这样？这样？这样？
You mean like this? And this? And this?

236
00:10:41,891 --> 00:10:45,728
‎-别闹了 格温！
‎-好了 我明白你们为什么吵架
-Quit it, Gwen!
-Okay, I understand why you're fighting.

237
00:10:45,811 --> 00:10:47,772
‎都是他害的
He… He <i>does</i> this to people.

238
00:10:47,855 --> 00:10:50,274
‎我们把他弄出去吧
Let's just get him out!

239
00:10:50,358 --> 00:10:51,651
‎我们把他弄出去吧
Get him out!

240
00:10:55,780 --> 00:10:57,698
‎-你会付出代价的
‎-你是在犯傻
-You're gonna pay.
-You're being an idiot.

241
00:10:57,782 --> 00:10:59,116
‎你的脸才犯傻
Your face is being an idiot.

242
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:02,495
‎-这话驴唇不对马嘴
‎-是啊 不对
-That doesn't even make sense.
-Yeah. It doesn't.

243
00:11:02,578 --> 00:11:03,454
[imitates explosion]

244
00:11:03,537 --> 00:11:06,916
[rock music playing]

245
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:09,794
‎藏货…在雷德手上
Red… has the stash.

246
00:11:09,877 --> 00:11:13,047
‎哦 好吧 稍等哈
Cool, cool. Yeah. Um, hang on one second.

247
00:11:14,674 --> 00:11:16,258
[muffled scream]

248
00:11:19,595 --> 00:11:20,763
‎那我们现在怎么办？
So what do we do now?

249
00:11:21,430 --> 00:11:22,431
‎没关系
It's okay.

250
00:11:22,515 --> 00:11:24,558
‎他自己还不知道
He doesn't even know he has it yet.

251
00:11:25,101 --> 00:11:25,935
‎对吧 奥兹？
Right, Ozzie?

252
00:11:26,435 --> 00:11:27,395
‎知道什么？
Has what?

253
00:11:27,895 --> 00:11:31,816
‎我只是一个纯真无辜的小孩子
‎倒霉碰上一群小混混
I'm just a sweet innocent kid who got
caught up with some no-good riffraff.

254
00:11:32,817 --> 00:11:34,777
‎你这个只顾自保的混蛋
You save-yourself son of a bitch.

255
00:11:36,362 --> 00:11:37,488
‎我敬重你
I respect that.

256
00:11:39,323 --> 00:11:41,367
‎-好了 赶紧去拿吧
‎-这就去
-Now, go get it.
-We will.

257
00:11:41,450 --> 00:11:46,038
‎我只是…想跟莉亚道别
‎以防再也见不到她了
I just… wanted to come say goodbye to Leia
in case I never saw her again.

258
00:11:46,622 --> 00:11:48,124
Aww. [laughs softly]

259
00:11:48,791 --> 00:11:50,084
‎你还去不去了？
Are we doing this?

260
00:12:02,346 --> 00:12:03,514
Uh…

261
00:12:04,598 --> 00:12:05,683
[Leia] Mm-hmm…

262
00:12:05,766 --> 00:12:08,352
‎莉亚…把手挪开呗
Leia… move your hands.

263
00:12:10,771 --> 00:12:12,231
‎我们又回到老地方了
And we're back to that.

264
00:12:13,941 --> 00:12:16,569
‎嗨 雪莉 听着 我还需要一些时间
Hi, Sherri. Listen.
I'm gonna need more time.

265
00:12:16,652 --> 00:12:19,363
‎我不知道还能拖多久
‎能干的全被他干完了
I don't know how much more I can stall.
He's done everything.

266
00:12:19,447 --> 00:12:21,657
‎我觉得我家的合页比你家的还安静
I think my hinges are quieter than yours.

267
00:12:21,741 --> 00:12:24,201
‎这个嘛…我看未必
Well… I doubt that.

268
00:12:24,285 --> 00:12:25,453
[laughs]

269
00:12:25,536 --> 00:12:28,164
‎你就…瞎编点由头 再见
Just… Just make something up. Bye.

270
00:12:30,624 --> 00:12:32,251
[screaming]

271
00:12:32,334 --> 00:12:33,335
‎怎么了？
What?

272
00:12:33,419 --> 00:12:36,797
‎我好像看到一只老鼠
‎很大 看起来就像半只耗子！
I think I just saw a mouse.
It was big. It looked half-rat!

273
00:12:36,881 --> 00:12:39,550
‎它马上就要一命呜呼了
Well, it's about to be all dead.

274
00:12:39,633 --> 00:12:42,303
[rock music playing]

275
00:12:43,012 --> 00:12:44,847
‎坚强大男孩在这里呢
Well, there's my big, strong boy.

276
00:12:44,930 --> 00:12:47,725
‎还是那句话…我有主儿了哈
Again… I'm spoken for.

277
00:12:49,018 --> 00:12:50,019
Oh.

278
00:12:50,686 --> 00:12:51,687
‎真可惜
What a shame.

279
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:57,485
‎-看看我从你的枕头底下拿了什么
‎-你拿这个做什么？
-Look what I took from under your pillow.
-What are you doing with that?

280
00:12:57,985 --> 00:13:00,154
‎她看起来挺横 但没有弗兰基毯毯
She looks all tough,
but she can't fall asleep

281
00:13:00,237 --> 00:13:01,530
‎她就睡不着
without Frankie the Blankie.

282
00:13:01,614 --> 00:13:03,407
‎他也需要我
He needs me too.

283
00:13:04,283 --> 00:13:07,536
‎你动我的东西 我就用弗兰基蹭屁股
You touch my stuff,
Frankie gets butt-flossed.

284
00:13:08,037 --> 00:13:09,955
‎-弗兰基！
‎-喂
-Frankie!
-Hey.

285
00:13:10,039 --> 00:13:11,832
[Gwen grunting]

286
00:13:11,916 --> 00:13:13,209
‎-滚开！
‎-不！
-Get off!
-No!

287
00:13:13,292 --> 00:13:14,293
[Nate grunting]

288
00:13:14,376 --> 00:13:16,170
‎好吧 那我去洗手间
Fine. Then I'm going to the bathroom.

289
00:13:16,253 --> 00:13:18,339
‎-我恨你！
‎-我恨你！
-Eww! I hate you!
-I hate you!

290
00:13:19,757 --> 00:13:21,175
‎我恨你
I hate you!

291
00:13:22,218 --> 00:13:26,263
[rock music playing]

292
00:13:27,139 --> 00:13:29,725
‎在这里呢 我们拿上赶紧走吧
There it is.
Let's grab it and get out of here.

293
00:13:29,809 --> 00:13:33,229
‎等等！这也太容易了
‎如果是陷阱呢？
Wait! This feels too easy.
What if it's a trap?

294
00:13:35,022 --> 00:13:36,148
‎你看太多动画…
You've seen too many car--

295
00:13:36,232 --> 00:13:37,858
‎-还真是陷阱！
‎-我就知道！
-[sharp snap]
-It's a trap!

296
00:13:37,942 --> 00:13:40,152
‎-还真是陷阱！
‎-我就知道！
I knew it! [screams]

297
00:13:40,236 --> 00:13:41,445
[trap snaps]

298
00:13:41,529 --> 00:13:43,072
[groans in pain]

299
00:13:43,155 --> 00:13:44,114
‎别动
Freeze!

300
00:13:45,658 --> 00:13:46,742
[trap snaps]

301
00:13:46,826 --> 00:13:47,910
‎该死
-Damn it!
-[trap snaps]

302
00:13:47,993 --> 00:13:49,036
Ow!

303
00:13:50,287 --> 00:13:51,747
‎这里简直是地狱！
This place is hell!

304
00:13:53,165 --> 00:13:55,584
‎这几乎和划水槽事件如出一辙
This is almost as bad as
the Slip 'N Slide incident.

305
00:13:55,668 --> 00:13:57,586
‎我家邻居康妮还得手把手…教我弄开
My neighbor Connie had to coach me through

306
00:13:58,087 --> 00:13:59,129
‎我家邻居康妮还得手把手…教我弄开
getting it out.

307
00:13:59,797 --> 00:14:02,341
‎哇 我家邻居连招呼都不打
Wow. My neighbors don't even wave hello.

308
00:14:02,967 --> 00:14:05,177
‎我讨厌这种怪怪的感觉
I hate how weird everything is.

309
00:14:05,261 --> 00:14:08,138
‎我希望能快进到你和内特的状态
I wish I could just fast-forward
to where you and Nate are.

310
00:14:08,222 --> 00:14:09,974
‎一切都很轻松
Where, like, things are easy. [scoffs]

311
00:14:10,057 --> 00:14:12,226
‎相信我 并不总是那么轻松
Believe me, it's not always easy.

312
00:14:13,644 --> 00:14:16,438
‎内特和我对未来的看法很不一样
Nate and I aren't really
on the same page about our futures.

313
00:14:16,522 --> 00:14:20,317
‎最近 我们总为各种事情瞎吵
Now, we're having
the dumbest fights about everything.

314
00:14:20,818 --> 00:14:22,695
‎比如遇上龙卷风怎么办
Like what to do if there's a tornado.

315
00:14:22,778 --> 00:14:24,780
‎我说躲进地下室
I say hide in a basement.

316
00:14:25,739 --> 00:14:26,657
‎他想当乘风少年
He wants to ride one.

317
00:14:27,658 --> 00:14:31,036
‎我只想说 事情永远不会完美
I'm just saying,
things are never going to be perfect.

318
00:14:31,954 --> 00:14:35,666
‎至于你跟杰伊那件事 确实很糟糕
And as for what happened with Jay,
sure, it was bad.

319
00:14:36,166 --> 00:14:38,210
‎但总不会比告诉大家更糟糕
But it's not gonna be
as bad as when we tell everyone.

320
00:14:38,294 --> 00:14:39,545
‎谢谢
Thanks.

321
00:14:40,379 --> 00:14:42,089
‎-我们拿到了
‎-是吗？
-We got it.
-You did?

322
00:14:42,756 --> 00:14:44,258
‎可能让我失去了一根脚趾
Might have cost me a toe.

323
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:46,969
‎我不敢看 但我感觉袜子湿了
I'm afraid to look, but my sock feels wet.

324
00:14:48,596 --> 00:14:50,681
‎嘿 刚才的事
Hey, so, about earlier.

325
00:14:50,764 --> 00:14:53,517
‎什么？我都不知道你在说什么
What? I don't even know
what you're talking about.

326
00:14:54,101 --> 00:14:56,687
‎他刚才一直念叨呢
Uh, that's <i>all</i> he talked about.

327
00:14:58,314 --> 00:15:01,692
‎我只是想太多
‎担心会把我们的关系搞得很怪
I just got in my head about us,
and I'm worried I made things weird.

328
00:15:01,775 --> 00:15:04,862
‎我们能不能忘掉之前
‎回到过去的样子？
Can we just forget about it
and go back to the way it was?

329
00:15:04,945 --> 00:15:06,655
‎比如你给我这一大块吻痕的时候？
Like when you gave me this huge hickey?

330
00:15:07,656 --> 00:15:10,034
‎-在哪儿来着？
‎-重点是…
-Where is it again?
-The point is…

331
00:15:11,035 --> 00:15:13,120
‎我希望我们之间可以开心舒服
I just want things to be
fun and comfortable again.

332
00:15:13,871 --> 00:15:15,998
‎那…你想要的就是我想要的
Well… I want what you want.

333
00:15:16,582 --> 00:15:18,584
‎很好 因我想要这个
Good, because this is what I want.

334
00:15:19,668 --> 00:15:20,586
‎你的脚趾好恶心！
Ew, your toe!

335
00:15:20,669 --> 00:15:21,795
‎我想看看
Ooh, I wanna see.

336
00:15:23,756 --> 00:15:24,840
‎你亲了我的耳朵
You kissed my ear.

337
00:15:24,924 --> 00:15:26,175
‎那你别转头啊！
Stop turning!

338
00:15:26,258 --> 00:15:28,969
[rock music playing]

339
00:15:30,095 --> 00:15:31,597
‎别冲我喘气
Stop breathing on me.

340
00:15:33,807 --> 00:15:36,018
‎好了 够了
-[loud, hissing exhale]
-Okay, that's enough.

341
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:39,021
‎你俩怎么回事？赶紧的 动手
What's your problem? Come on. Chop-chop.

342
00:15:39,104 --> 00:15:40,105
‎好吧
Fine.

343
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:44,944
‎它不是普通的衬衫 是我爸送的
[scoffs] That wasn't just any shirt.
It's from my dad.

344
00:15:45,027 --> 00:15:47,154
‎-但你穿根本不合身
‎-这不重要
-But it didn't even fit you.
-It doesn't matter.

345
00:15:47,237 --> 00:15:50,366
‎他亲自买了放进箱子里
He went out and bought it
and… and put it in the box.

346
00:15:50,449 --> 00:15:53,118
‎是他亲自动手的
His hands were on it. [sighs]

347
00:15:53,202 --> 00:15:56,163
‎你不会明白的
‎你比我更常见到自己的爸爸
You wouldn't understand.
You see your dad way more than I do.

348
00:15:56,246 --> 00:15:58,082
‎没错 但我还是很想他
Yeah, but I still miss him.

349
00:15:58,165 --> 00:16:01,418
‎我只有在他经过这里
‎去另一个城市时才能见到他
I only ever get to see him when he comes
through town on his way to another city.

350
00:16:01,502 --> 00:16:03,170
‎马戏团演员？
Circus performer?

351
00:16:04,964 --> 00:16:06,382
‎这是开的哪路脑洞？
How is <i>that</i> your first guess?

352
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:09,551
‎他是卡车司机
He's a truck driver.

353
00:16:10,928 --> 00:16:14,348
‎不过 如果我知道你的感受
‎我就绝不会动它
But, Nate, if I'd known how you felt,
I never would have touched it.

354
00:16:14,431 --> 00:16:15,432
‎也不会剪
Or cut it up.

355
00:16:16,141 --> 00:16:18,644
‎或者让车子碾过做旧
Or let cars run over it
to make it look vintage.

356
00:16:20,020 --> 00:16:21,438
‎没关系 反正很傻
It's fine. It's dumb.

357
00:16:21,939 --> 00:16:23,107
‎不 一点都不傻
No, it's not dumb.

358
00:16:23,190 --> 00:16:24,525
‎这对我们俩来说都很糟糕
It sucks for both of us.

359
00:16:25,985 --> 00:16:28,070
‎大笨蛋 你把我弄哭了
You idiot. You made me cry.

360
00:16:29,738 --> 00:16:31,573
‎-我恨你
‎-我也恨你
-I hate you.
-I hate you too.

361
00:16:33,575 --> 00:16:34,952
‎我也想爸爸
I miss my dad too.

362
00:16:36,829 --> 00:16:40,082
‎在我十岁生日的时候
‎他带我去看赛狗
He took me to the dog track
on my tenth birthday.

363
00:16:40,582 --> 00:16:42,626
‎还让我抿了一口他的啤酒
And he gave me a sip of his beer,

364
00:16:42,710 --> 00:16:45,462
‎我把爆米花吐出来了
‎而且还是爆米花的形状
and I barfed up my popcorn,

365
00:16:45,546 --> 00:16:48,048
‎我把爆米花吐出来了
‎而且还是爆米花的形状
and it still looked like popcorn.

366
00:16:51,510 --> 00:16:53,762
‎雷德回来了！他就在我后面！
Red's coming! He's right behind me!

367
00:16:54,847 --> 00:16:57,266
‎他拄着拐棍儿 我们可能还有时间
He's got that cane,
so maybe we've got some time.

368
00:16:58,183 --> 00:16:59,727
‎内特 马上把驼鹿弄走
Nate, moose, now.

369
00:16:59,810 --> 00:17:00,769
‎我来帮你
Let me help you.

370
00:17:00,853 --> 00:17:03,105
‎-谢了 老妹
‎-有我呢 老哥
-Thanks, sis. [chuckles]
-I got you, big bro.

371
00:17:03,689 --> 00:17:06,150
‎我家孩子怎么这么懂事？
‎他们偷喝你家酒了？
Why are my kids being nice?
Did they get into your wine?

372
00:17:06,734 --> 00:17:09,403
‎没有 我们…就是小感动了一下
No. We… We had an emotional moment.

373
00:17:09,903 --> 00:17:11,697
‎他们都很想念爸爸
They both were missing their dads.

374
00:17:11,780 --> 00:17:12,740
Oh.

375
00:17:12,823 --> 00:17:15,159
‎哎 听这话 我就像挨了窝心脚
Man, that's always a gut punch.

376
00:17:15,242 --> 00:17:17,036
‎不 这又不是世界末日
No. It wasn't the end of the world.

377
00:17:17,119 --> 00:17:20,998
‎内特的爸爸
‎给他寄了一件T恤衫 但是太小了
No, no. Nate's father sent him a T-shirt.
It was too small.

378
00:17:21,081 --> 00:17:22,833
‎格温拿去了 现在没事了
Gwen took it. It's okay now.

379
00:17:22,916 --> 00:17:24,293
‎天杀的布莱恩
Frickin' Brian.

380
00:17:26,086 --> 00:17:29,006
‎我尽我所能让孩子们高兴
I try to do whatever I can
to make sure my kids never feel bad,

381
00:17:29,089 --> 00:17:31,216
‎可还是不小心整骚包了
but sometimes things
slip through my cracks.

382
00:17:34,845 --> 00:17:36,972
‎这号码…好长
That's… That's a lot of numbers.

383
00:17:39,683 --> 00:17:40,893
‎布莱恩 是我
Brian, it's me.

384
00:17:41,769 --> 00:17:43,854
‎我管你现在是日本几点呢？
‎反正我在威斯康辛
What the hell do I care
what time it is in Japan?

385
00:17:43,937 --> 00:17:45,647
‎我管你现在是日本几点呢？
‎反正我在威斯康辛
I'm in Wisconsin. [scoffs]

386
00:17:46,231 --> 00:17:48,734
‎是啊 我…
Yeah, I…

387
00:17:52,237 --> 00:17:55,032
‎你好歹给儿子寄件合身的衣服啊
You need to send your son
a shirt that actually fits.

388
00:17:55,115 --> 00:17:57,117
‎他都跟你姐一样高了
He's as tall as your sister now.

389
00:17:57,201 --> 00:17:59,495
‎还有 告诉你床上那娘们儿 把嘴闭上
And tell that broad in your bed
to close her mouth.

390
00:17:59,578 --> 00:18:01,080
‎我能听到她打呼
I can hear her snorin'!

391
00:18:01,705 --> 00:18:03,082
‎她在跟日本通电话
She's on the phone with Japan.

392
00:18:03,165 --> 00:18:04,458
‎日本？
Japan?

393
00:18:04,958 --> 00:18:05,918
‎再见您呐
Sayonara.

394
00:18:06,001 --> 00:18:09,797
[funky rock music playing]

395
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:12,382
‎虾鱼天就得这么过
Now, <i>this</i> is you spend a dainy ray.

396
00:18:13,550 --> 00:18:14,551
‎下雨癫
Rainy dray.

397
00:18:16,095 --> 00:18:17,096
‎天
Day.

398
00:18:18,430 --> 00:18:20,099
‎喂 小心
Hey, be careful.

399
00:18:20,182 --> 00:18:22,476
‎在屋里开伞会倒霉的
It's bad luck to open a brella inside.

400
00:18:24,144 --> 00:18:25,145
‎等等
Hold up.

401
00:18:26,021 --> 00:18:27,231
‎再说一次
Say that word again.

402
00:18:28,023 --> 00:18:28,941
‎伞
Brella.

403
00:18:29,024 --> 00:18:31,860
‎每次下雨 妈就想不起那是啥玩意儿
Like, when it's raining, and Mom can
never remember what they're called,

404
00:18:31,944 --> 00:18:35,989
‎她总说：“把你们的咦…伞拿上”
and she's always like,
"Take your, um… brella."

405
00:18:36,073 --> 00:18:37,950
[both laughing]

406
00:18:38,033 --> 00:18:39,201
‎不是吧
No way!

407
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:43,372
[both chuckling]

408
00:18:44,498 --> 00:18:45,374
‎伞
Brella.

409
00:18:50,129 --> 00:18:52,131
‎等等 他是不是很火辣？
Wait, is he hot?

410
00:18:53,215 --> 00:18:54,508
Uh…

411
00:18:54,591 --> 00:18:55,509
‎是呢
Yeah.

412
00:18:59,847 --> 00:19:01,431
‎喂 雨停了
Hey, it stopped raining.

413
00:19:02,766 --> 00:19:05,352
‎她说得对 我们出去吧
[gasps] She's right. Let's get outta here.

414
00:19:05,435 --> 00:19:07,437
["No Rain" by Blind Melon playing]

415
00:19:12,401 --> 00:19:18,031
<i>♪ All I can say</i>
<i>Is that my life is pretty plain ♪</i>

416
00:19:18,115 --> 00:19:23,120
<i>♪ I like watching the puddles</i>
<i>Gather rain ♪</i>

417
00:19:25,080 --> 00:19:30,335
<i>♪ You know I'd like to keep</i>
<i>My cheeks dry today, hey ♪</i>

418
00:19:31,587 --> 00:19:35,883
<i>♪ So stay with me and I'll have it made ♪</i>

419
00:19:36,967 --> 00:19:42,681
<i>♪ And I don't understand</i>
<i>Why I sleep all day ♪</i>

420
00:19:43,432 --> 00:19:47,477
<i>♪ And I start to complain</i>
<i>That there's no rain… ♪</i>

421
00:19:47,561 --> 00:19:48,937
[song fades out]

422
00:19:49,021 --> 00:19:51,023
‎你们记得是怎么出来的吗？
Do you guys remember coming out here?

423
00:19:51,773 --> 00:19:52,608
‎不记得
No.

424
00:19:53,108 --> 00:19:56,653
‎但我很高兴我们出来了
‎今天过得很不错
But I'm glad we did.
It ended up being a pretty solid day.

425
00:19:58,989 --> 00:20:00,449
‎我希望这一切永远不要结束
I hope this never ends.

426
00:20:00,532 --> 00:20:02,659
‎孩子们 你们的课表来了
Kids, your school schedules came!

427
00:20:02,743 --> 00:20:04,661
‎夏天终于结束了 终于可以消停了
Summer is finally over.

428
00:20:04,745 --> 00:20:06,580
‎夏天终于结束了 终于可以消停了
All this is gonna end.

429
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:11,543
[rock music playing]

430
00:20:12,502 --> 00:20:15,422
[rock music playing]

431
00:20:48,789 --> 00:20:52,459
‎字幕翻译：Zeo Niu

